2010: A magnitude 7.5 earthquake on the Richter scale struck one of the Mentawai Islands off the coast of Sumatra, causing a tsunami of more than 10 meters [10 feet] that destroyed dozens of villages and claimed about 300 lives.
2016: A shallow earthquake struck the Pidie Regency in Atjeh, causing devastation and panic, as people were reminded of the devastation of the deadly 2004 earthquake and tsunami.
